<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12042&amp;p=136707#p136707"><![CDATA[
No, because the screen is basically working as a resonator which white will be easy to pick up and then also give you a whatever khz resonance you need. If the resonance is off, it won't work. Full on-&gt;Not working, Full off then on=60Hz resonance at best alternating=# khz needed.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4311">3gengames</a> — Thu Nov 20, 2014 7:25 pm</p><hr />
